{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The layout follows a vertical structure, prioritizing the hero image at the top, followed by product details, seller information, and finally, the 'Contact Seller' button.  Top and bottom navigation bars are included for seamless navigation within the app.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flow is designed to be intuitive and efficient. The prominent hero image immediately captures attention, followed by essential product information. The 'Contact Seller' button is positioned for easy access, enabling users to quickly initiate contact if needed.",
    "componentChoices": "I chose the 'Image carousel' component for displaying product photos, 'Text components' for product title, price, seller information, and the 'Button component' for the prominent 'Contact Seller' CTA. I chose the 'Avatar component' for seller profile images.  I chose 'appbar' and 'Bottom navigation' components for top and bottom navigation respectively over other navigation options like tabs or side drawers because of the simplicity and clarity for mobile.  The reference designs showcase their suitability for mobile e-commerce contexts.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established using a combination of size, color, and placement.  The hero image occupies the largest portion of the screen, immediately drawing the user's eye.  Headings are larger than body text, and the 'Contact Seller' button is highlighted through both size and color.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "For the 'Contact Seller' button, I selected the 'Filled', 'Large', 'Green' variants instead of 'Outlined' or 'Text' variants, and 'Medium' or 'Small' sizes because its prominence is essential for conversion purposes. A large, filled button emphasizes the action.  The green color aligns with our primary call-to-action color palette. The reference images showcase the button design effectively.",
    "colorSelectionRationale": "Selected color style 'Primary/primary50' from colorStyles.primary for the 'Contact Seller' button background because it is the most prominent primary color in the palette and readily available. Selected color style 'Neutral/neutral90' from colorStyles.neutral for background and 'Neutral/neutral50' from colorStyles.neutral for text colors because of their readability and consistency with the rest of the UI.",
    "nativeElementJustification": "With moment significance of 0.7 and conversion-critical business impact, this product detail screen warrants enhanced treatment. Native rectangle component with a subtle background gradient adds a layer of visual appeal, complementing the product photography.  The systematic design approach using specified components assures that the core functionality is not compromised while the enhanced visual aspects elevate the shopping experience."
  }
}
```

